#: portal/templates/international.royalsociety.org.nz/profile_section.html:75
#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:94
msgid ""
"A First Stage Researcher conducts research under supervision. This may "
"include PhD and research masters students."
msgstr ""
"Ko tā te Kairangahau Taumata Tuatahi he whakahaere rangahau i raro i tētahi "
"kaiwhakahaere tikanga. Ka tae atu pea tēnei ki ngā tauira kairangi me ngā "
"tauira rangahau tohu paerua."

#: portal/templates/international.royalsociety.org.nz/profile_section.html:78
#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:97
msgid "Emerging Researcher"
msgstr "Kairangahau Awhero"

#: portal/templates/international.royalsociety.org.nz/profile_section.html:79
#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:98
msgid ""
"An Emerging Researcher has made a contribution through original research by "
"developing a substantial body of work, innovation or application which may "
"merit national or internationally refereed publications, patents, and papers "
"at conferences and congresses."
msgstr ""
"He whai hua ngā mahi rangahau tūturu a te Kairangahau Awhero nā tana "
"waihanga i tētahi putanga mahi kūpara, aronga hou, taupānga rānei e whai "
"take ai pea ki ngā pānuitanga ka arotakengia ā-motu, ā-ao rānei, ngā mana "
"waihanga, me ngā tuhinga ka tukuna ki ngā wānanga me ngā hui taumata."

#: portal/templates/international.royalsociety.org.nz/profile_section.html:82
#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:101
msgid "Established Researcher"
msgstr "Kairangahau Pūmau"

#: portal/templates/international.royalsociety.org.nz/profile_section.html:83
#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:102
msgid ""
"An Established Researcher identifies research problems and opportunities "
"within their area of expertise, conducts research independently which "
"advances a research agenda, can form research consortia, and secure research "
"funding/budgets from funding agencies or industry, publishes papers as lead "
"author, acts as a mentor for other researchers."
msgstr ""
"Ko tā te Kairangahau Pūmau he tautohu i ngā raruraru rangahau me ngā āheinga "
"kei tōna kaupapa mātanga, he motuhake tana whakahaere rangahau e kōkiritia "
"ai tētahi kaupapa rangahau, he āhei ki te whakarite tōpūtanga rangahau, me "
"te punga pūtea/tahua rangahau mai i ngā umanga pūtea, ahumahi rānei, he "
"whakaputa tuhinga ko ia te kaituhi matua, he whakaruruhau hoki mō ētahi atu "
"kairangahau."

#: portal/templates/international.royalsociety.org.nz/profile_section.html:86
#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:105
msgid "Leading Researcher"
msgstr "Kairangahau Matua"

#: portal/templates/international.royalsociety.org.nz/profile_section.html:87
#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:106
msgid ""
"A Leading Researcher has an international reputation based on research "
"excellence in their field and a proven record of securing significant "
"research funding.  This researcher is a professional development role model "
"for others. They focus on long term team planning and career paths for "
"researchers, securing funding for team positions."
msgstr ""
"He rongonui i te ao te Kairangahau Matua nā runga i te hiranga o te rangahau "
"i tōna kaupapa me tana pai ki te punga pūtea rangahau hira. He tauira "
"akoranga ngaio tēnei kairangahau mō ētahi atu. Ka arotahi ki ngā mahere pae "
"tawhiti ā-rōpū me ngā ara umanga mō ngā kairangahau, te punga pūtea mō ngā "
"tūranga rōpū hoki."

#: portal/templates/international.royalsociety.org.nz/profile_section.html:91
